-- Aston Villa Hires Norwich Coach Paul Lambert to Replace McLeish
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-06-02T11:35:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-02/aston-villa-hires-norwich-coach-paul-lambert-to-replace-mcleish.html
Aston Villa  hired Norwich’s Paul
Lambert as its manager, the Premier League club said in a
statment on its website.  Lambert, 42, replaces  Alex McLeish , who was fired May 14
after just one season. Villa finished 16th in the Premier League
last season, two points and two places above the three-team
relegation zone.  “The board of Aston Villa are delighted to confirm Paul
Lambert has been appointed Villa manager,” the one-line club
statement read.  Lambert joined Norwich in 2009 when the club was in the
third tier of English soccer. He guided the Canaries to two
straight promotions and a 12th-place finish in the Premier
League last season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
